2026-04-21 01:28:33 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['control module switch'] hypothesis_explanation='Measurements show 12 V at the control-module input pair but only ~0.36 V at the output pair. Across the switch there is ~12 V on the supply side and ~0.36 V on the load side, and the switch tests as an open circuit with no continuity in either position. This means the switch contacts are not closing, so the series path from PSU to load is interrupted inside the control module. With the switch failed open, the red inverted-cable LED remains off (no current) and the load module never receives 12 V, so the main lamp does not turn on. Replacing/repairing the control-module switch should restore normal operation.'
